  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws and regulations targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Report large cash transactions\n2. Implement customer identification programs\n3. Screen for suspicious financial activities\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Cooperate with law enforcement investigations\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution. International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) also develop global standards to combat money laundering.",
